    <div id="School-Day" class="content-section">
      <h1>School Day</h1>
      <p>Learn about our daily schedule and activities for Pre-Prep students.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Arrival:</strong> 7:30am – 8:00am. Warm greetings and morning activities.</li>
        <li><strong>Morning Circle:</strong> 8:00am – 8:30am. Songs, calendar, and weather discussions.</li>
        <li><strong>Core Learning:</strong> 8:30am – 10:00am. Phonics, numbers, and early literacy activities.</li>
        <li><strong>Snack Break:</strong> 10:00am – 10:30am. Healthy snacks and social time.</li>
        <li><strong>Creative Play:</strong> 10:30am – 11:30am. Art, building blocks, and imaginative play.</li>
        <li><strong>Outdoor Activities:</strong> 11:30am – 12:00pm. Physical play and exploration.</li>
        <li><strong>Lunch:</strong> 12:00pm – 1:00pm. Nutritious lunch and quiet time.</li>
        <li><strong>Afternoon Session:</strong> 1:00pm – 2:30pm. Story time, music, and themed activities.</li>
        <li><strong>Pick-Up:</strong> 2:30pm – 3:00pm. Daily feedback and parent communication.</li>
      </ul>
      <img src="/images/people/successful-schoolgirl_1098-13593.avif" alt="Pre-Prep Activities" style="max-width: 100%; margin-top: 1em; border-radius: 8px;" loading="lazy">
    </div>

    <div id="Curriculum" class="content-section">
      <h1>Curriculum</h1>
      <p>Our Pre-Prep curriculum is designed to foster holistic development through play-based learning and age-appropriate activities.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Language & Literacy:</strong> Phonics, letter recognition, vocabulary building, and early writing.</li>
        <li><strong>Mathematics:</strong> Number concepts, counting, shapes, patterns, and basic problem-solving.</li>
        <li><strong>Science Exploration:</strong> Simple experiments, nature observation, and sensory activities.</li>
        <li><strong>Creative Arts:</strong> Drawing, painting, music, movement, and dramatic play.</li>
        <li><strong>Physical Education:</strong> Motor skills, coordination, and healthy habits.</li>
        <li><strong>Social & Emotional Skills:</strong> Self-regulation, empathy, and communication.</li>
        <li><strong>Faith & Character:</strong> Bible stories, prayers, and Christian values.</li>
      </ul>
      <img src="/images/people/other-uniform.jfif" alt="Pre-Prep Curriculum" style="max-width: 100%; margin-top: 1em; border-radius: 8px;" loading="lazy">
